-- Egyptian Stocks: Orascom Telecom Media and Oriental Weavers
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-06-13T13:30:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/egyptian-stocks-orascom-telecom-media-maridive-oil-services.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX30 Index (EGX30)  fell
for the third time in four days, declining 0.6 percent to
4,421.38 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo.  The following shares were active on the Egyptian Exchange.
Stock symbols follow company names.  Orascom Telecom Media & Technology Holding SAE (OTMT)  
climbed 4.7 percent to 1.35 Egyptian pounds, the highest level
in almost three weeks. The stock surged a second day after the
board recommended a dividend of 1.05 Egyptian pounds a share for
the period ending June 7.  Oriental Weavers Co. (ORWE)   gained as much as 1.2
percent to 16.1 pounds before closing at 15.94 pounds, the
highest level in more than two weeks. The Arab country’s biggest
carpets manufacturer plans to invest 200 million pounds ($33
million) on expansion projects this year including the second
phase of a production facility starting in the fourth quarter,
Al Borsa newspaper reported.  -- Editors: Robert Lakin, Tim Farrand  To contact the reporter on this story:
